Suh says, in the R, that they used to call the water-skin"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajobN","text_ar":"شَجْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and they used not to hold it otherwise than suspended, so that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi$ojabN","text_ar":"مِشْجَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick, to which the water-skin is suspended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"then they amplified the application of this word so as to call thereby the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing upon which clothes are suspended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAjibu","text_ar":"مَشَاجِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)"}],"source_refs":["T","Msb","K","Nh","TA","S","MF"]}]}}